transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I'm glad I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'd like to cancel my subscription for a while.

Speaker 1: Sure, I could take a look into your account.

Speaker 2: What's your last name and zip code?

Speaker 1: Okay, it's Voinovich. V-O-I-N-O-V-I-C-H.

Speaker 2: And the zip is 65624.

Speaker 1: Okay, I pulled you up here. So one option

Speaker 2: I can actually give you because I do see you're one of our VIP members. Instead of cancelling it out,

Speaker 1: I could just go ahead and put you on the six-month freeze.

Speaker 2: It gives you the option to call us to get it sooner or to push it another six months.

Speaker 1: That way you don't lose out on your discounted rate as well.

Speaker 2: Um...

Speaker 1: I'd just assume go ahead and cancel it for now and if I meet, you know, down the line—

Speaker 2: The main reason I bring that up too is because the thing is the prescription is attached to the refill date.

Speaker 1: The moment we cancel out the date, what it does is it actually deletes the visit from the doctor's end.

Speaker 2: I mean, that you wouldn't be able to order this in the future because the doctor won't create another visit since we kind of—

Speaker 1: Pay for that first visit.

Speaker 2: But if you do freeze it out,

Speaker 1: You're gonna always just reach back out to us to order it whenever you would want it or you could just delay it

Speaker 2: For another half year. We have no problem with that whatsoever. At least our prescription remains active in the system.

Speaker 1: Okay, that'll work.

Speaker 2: Sure, I'll go ahead and make that adjustment to your account right now and you're all set on that part.

Speaker 1: Give us a call back if you have any other questions or you need it sooner.

Speaker 2: But other than that, I hope you have a good day.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thank you. No problem. Bye. Bye. Bye.
